---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Nibble & Noble"
  description="Who writes Nibble & Noble, and what this critic journal is for."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl flex-1 px-4 py-10 sm:px-6 sm:py-14">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-semibold text-nn-cream sm:text-4xl">About</h1>
    <div class="nn-prose mt-8 max-w-none px-0">
      <p>
        <strong class="text-nn-cream">Nibble & Noble</strong> is a food critic blog built as a calm, dark reading
        room—closer to a notebook margin than a billboard. The reviews are long-form on purpose: restaurants are small
        worlds, and shortcuts usually show up in the prose before they show up in the cooking.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is a template you can grow: add your byline, your city, your ethics statement, and your own voice.
        What stays constant is the shape—venue, context, meal, verdict—so readers know what kind of contract they are
        signing when they scroll.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you are an editor (human or agent), start with the <code>agents.md</code> file in the project root for stack
        notes, content conventions, and design tokens.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
